<p><font color="#FF0000">&gt;&gt;&gt;</font>In the middle of a big
cross country trip, I happened to print out some names of folks off
the AIRS list from Seattle to San Francisco, and damn if I didn't
use it. Just 30 miles out of Seattle i threw a rod in my 71 camper
bus. Arggh! No worry, I called a few folks off of the list, one of
them (Terry Tacker of Puyallup) towed me with a special bus towbar,
and another (Fred Stoermer of Tacoma?) came just to see how things
went. They recommended Ovals Motor Sports of Federal Way. I had a
rebuilt engine put in, and after several days of diagnosing heating
problems, Oval's got me back on the road. Thanks to all in the area
for their help and concern, and Oval's for being patient with a
weary traveler and helping to solve the overheating problems!</p>
